[Baron Dr. F. v. Muller in Melbourne has had the great goodness to send me a sample of manna from Eucalyptus viminalis, that interesting substance which has been studied by Thomson, Virey, and especially Johnston and Berthelot, and a compilation of the existing notes on which is to be found in the great work of F. v. Müller (Eucalyptographia l0th. Decade Eucal. Vimin.).



      B84.11.02, which on the final page of the entry for E. viminalis cites the work of these and other chemists. See also M to F. Basedow, December 1885 (in this edition as 85-12-00d).
